## 2️⃣  `pcapng.ml` – thin OCaml wrapper

Only a few `external` declarations are needed; the heavy lifting lives in the
C stub.

```ocaml
(* ---------------------------------------------------------------------- *)
(*  pcapsng.ml – thin wrapper that declares the C primitives                 *)
(* ---------------------------------------------------------------------- *)

type t = private int   (* the concrete representation is a custom block *)

type frame = {
  ts          : float;
  data        : bytes;
  original_len: int;
}

external open_file : string -> t = "caml_pcapng_open_file"
external close     : t -> unit = "caml_pcapng_close"
external iter      : (frame -> unit) -> t -> unit = "caml_pcapng_iter"
external fold      : ('a -> frame -> 'a) -> 'a -> t -> 'a = "caml_pcapng_fold"
external next      : t -> frame option = "caml_pcapng_next"
```

